        <h2 class="content-h2">Why <em>Four Aspects</em> Matter Together</h2>
        <p class="content-p">
          Most orthopedic treatments focus only on the injury itself — the torn ligament, the inflamed joint, the stress fracture. But Dr. Sarish Sharma's approach goes deeper. He addresses the <strong>underlying nutritional and metabolic deficiencies</strong> that are silently making injuries worse, delaying recovery, and causing new injuries to occur.
        </p>
        <p class="content-p">
          In a single injection session, all four critical aspects are addressed simultaneously — saving time, reducing clinic visits, and delivering superior outcomes compared to treating each deficiency separately over multiple weeks.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- 4 Aspects -->
      <div class="content-section">
        <div class="content-label">The Four Pillars</div>
        <h2 class="content-h2">What We <em>Address in One Session</em></h2>
        <div class="aspect-grid">

          <div class="aspect-card inflammation">
            <div class="aspect-num">01</div>
            <div class="aspect-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-fire"></i></div>
            <h4>Inflammation Control</h4>
            <p>Chronic low-grade inflammation is present in most musculoskeletal injuries and significantly impairs healing. Targeted anti-inflammatory injections reduce inflammatory markers, relieve pain, and create the right environment for tissue repair.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="aspect-card vitd">
            <div class="aspect-num">02</div>
            <div class="aspect-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-sun"></i></div>
            <h4>Vitamin D3</h4>
            <p>Vitamin D3 deficiency affects over 70% of Indians due to limited sun exposure and dietary gaps. It plays a critical role in calcium absorption, bone mineralisation, muscle function, and immune regulation. Deficiency directly leads to weak bones and increased fracture risk.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="aspect-card vitb">
            <div class="aspect-num">03</div>
            <div class="aspect-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-capsules"></i></div>
            <h4>Vitamin B12</h4>
            <p>B12 deficiency is extremely common in India — particularly in vegetarians — and causes nerve inflammation, fatigue, and impaired motor function. In athletes and active individuals, B12 deficiency slows muscle recovery, causes unexplained pain, and contributes to stress fractures.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="aspect-card bmd">
            <div class="aspect-num">04</div>
            <div class="aspect-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-bone"></i></div>
            <h4>Bone Mineral Density</h4>
            <p>Low BMD is the silent cause of stress fractures, recurring joint pain, and osteoporosis — often undetected until a fracture occurs. Correcting BMD through targeted therapy prevents future injuries and strengthens the skeletal framework that supports all physical activity.</p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>

