          Despite India being a sun-rich country, nutritional deficiencies are alarmingly common. The combination of predominantly vegetarian diets, indoor lifestyles, and limited awareness means millions of Indians are walking around with deficiencies that directly cause pain, injury, and slow recovery — without even knowing it.
        </p>
